(i) she arrived unexpectedly at her neighbour’s apartment, around 11:30 at night;

(ii) she was upset and crying;

(iii) she asked that the police be called;

(iv) she spontaneously described and demonstrated the incident which brought her to her neighbours and prompted the report to the police;

(v) she repeated a consistent version to the police;

